<subSubSection id="83C12E3F5306F2444FD75899BFD13440" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="7D6E7F0966A00C00421846E948C6731E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2092C441BBA45AA6511C1A70DBEB0750" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Entirely glabrous, twining perennial or liana; stems often granulose. Leaves petiolate, 3-8 
<normalizedToken id="C62B75ADC16BA6A87A0E347C840327CE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-6 cm, oblong-ovate to ovate, acute, base cordate, the auricles acute or rounded, abaxially paler; petioles 2-6.5 cm. Inflorescence of rather dense axillary pedunculate cymes; peduncles 5-10 cm; bracteoles ovate, c. 2 mm, caducous; pedicels short, 0.5-1.7 cm; sepals unequal, outer 1-3 
<normalizedToken id="154CAE9AE5D4B27FF52E3266E0DF63F8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, suborbicular to elliptic, the margin scarious, inner 7-8 
<normalizedToken id="633D0D6625442FA235C6BA58FF742F70" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, oblong-elliptic, rounded; corolla 5-6 cm long, funnel shaped, white with a purple tube, glabrous, limb c. 5 cm diam., the midpetaline bands terminating in small teeth. Capsules ovoid, 8-9 
<normalizedToken id="6BBA00D3F91DB6650805E078D08DC53E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-7 mm, glabrous, rostrate, the persistent style 4-5 mm long; seeds 7 
<normalizedToken id="BFE44DDD25DC450E229A63CAB34A3087" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 mm, densely white-pubescent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
