<subSubSection id="A1985775972113EBE96BCD00502D40DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9B2B6312811365C28695DC2D74906D32" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3FD47968A1959EA08E809BB481255D2B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Very close to 
<taxonomicName id="45219D02D6B79798F56CD07E23A5271B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squamosa">
<emphasis id="AC701191C97C81DA04E1B5BBE3E4A03C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea squamosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing in being always glabrous with shorter outer sepals and a white corolla limb. The seeds are densely uniformly pubescent, rather than woolly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F034324046774EA8BFFB022E69D53EB3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
We have been cautious in accepting South American records of this species, which may have been confused with 
<taxonomicName id="F52E385E6D9EE9FD3201FF31D2F53689" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cryptica">
<emphasis id="150FCE09F0FA9AFAA5858197F1194D9D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea cryptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as with 
<taxonomicName id="FB0C4A64FEEA9D60C4322EF5F939925E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squamosa">
<emphasis id="3588A75E14F8DA9DF3BCBD592CC9B32E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. squamosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
